The paper focuses on generating adversarial examples for visual recognition tasks using 3D meshes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper makes use of a differentiable renderer to manipulate the shape and texture of objects, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the attack on classifiers and object detectors, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses a pipeline for performing black-box attacks, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
